ld_Athletics\", \"score\": 0.9999999999340616, \"rank\": 6.576239556190523e-11, \"text\": \"World Athletics\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Athletics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Athletics\"}, {\"begin\": 2227, \"end\": 2258, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"International Olympic Committee\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"its prize money\", \"from\": 2173, \"to\": 2188}, {\"ngram\": \"the revenue\", \"from\": 2194, \"to\": 2205}]}, {\"sentence\": \"That should also include individual professional sport organizations such as the USTA or USGA, which would then allow collegiate tennis players and golfers to earn prize money while maintaining collegiate eligibility.\", \"from\": 2260, \"to\": 2477, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"individual professional sport organizations\", \"from\": 2285, \"to\": 2328}, {\"ngram\": \"the USTA\", \"from\": 2337, \"to\": 2345}, {\"ngram\": \"USGA\", \"from\": 2349, \"to\": 2353}, {\"ngram\": \"collegiate tennis players\", \"from\": 2378, \"to\": 2403}, {\"ngram\": \"golfers\", \"from\": 2408, \"to\": 2415}, {\"ngram\": \"prize money\", \"from\": 2424, \"to\": 2435}, {\"ngram\": \"collegiate eligibility\", \"from\": 2454, \"to\": 2476}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Advertisement Such circumstances are the heart ofa lawsuit filed by University of North Carolina tennis player Reese Brantmeier, who is arguing that she and other athletes like her deserve to keep the prize money they earn by participating in and winning tournaments.\", \"from\": 2479, \"to\": 2747, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Such circumstances\", \"from\": 2493, \"to\": 2511}, {\"ngram\": \"the heart\", \"from\": 2516, \"to\": 2525}, {\"ngram\": \"ofa\", \"from\": 2526, \"to\": 2529}, {\"ngram\": \"lawsuit\", \"from\": 2530, \"to\": 2537}, {\"ngram\": \"North Carolina\", \"from\": 2561, \"to\": 2575}, {\"ngram\": \"other athletes\", \"from\": 2636, \"to\": 2650}, {\"ngram\": \"the prize money\", \"from\": 2676, \"to\": 2691}, {\"ngram\": \"tournaments\", \"from\": 2734, \"to\": 2745}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Right now, they can only keep enough to cover their expenses.\", \"from\": 2748, \"to\": 2809, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"their expenses\", \"from\": 2794, \"to\": 2808}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Meanwhile \\u2026 these athletes see Caitlin Clark appearing in national television commercials and quarterbacks hawking headphones through lucrative name, image and likeness (NIL) deals while maintaining their NCAA eligibility.\", \"from\": 2811, \"to\": 3033, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2842, \"end\": 2855, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Caitlin_Clark\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Caitlin Clark\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Caitlin_Clark\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Caitlin_Clark\"}, {\"begin\": 2981, \"end\": 2984, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Student_athlete_compensation\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.639370450880351e-32, \"text\": \"NIL\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Student_athlete_compensation\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Student_athlete_compensation\"}, {\"begin\": 3016, \"end\": 3020, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Collegiate_Athletic_Association\", \"score\": 0.9999999960696186, \"rank\": 3.929836183794518e-09, \"text\": \"NCAA\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Collegiate_Athletic_Association\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Collegiate_Athletic_Association\"}], \"noun_phra